00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm allergic to dyes...

282
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Thus, before reaching the destination, I choose to take a detour</i>

283
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>For those we hold dear to us are the ones who break our heart</i>

284
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>For those we hold dear to us are the ones</i>

285
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Who break our heart...</i>

286
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just one regret, though.

287
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I know...

288
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You shouldn't have said you're marrying Gulrez.

289
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No.

290
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I shouldn't have slapped him.

291
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure he doesn't regret being slapped.

292
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He ought to.

293
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hmm... Touché...

294
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I guess being booted out hurts much more.

295
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who booted him out?

296
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You.

297
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You booted him in the face, more or less.

298
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But he's a good actor.

299
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He didn't let anyone know.

300
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you think he'd go back

301
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
To his English roses?

302
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
May he go to Hell. Like I care.

303
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who knows, he may even get married to Jiya in his fury!

304
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So?

305
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you care?

306
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't give two boots.

307
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why d'you lie?

308
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's what happened during the match.

309
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Everything was fine.

310
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Until

311
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The bell rang and he didn't come back.

312
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
When we found out Jiya took him along?

313
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You were waiting for half an hour.

314
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He got late, but he got back.

315
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Your face was too red by then though.

316
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You turned the match into a proper mismatch.

317
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What d'you mean?

318
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's the problem with you.

319
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You ask others the meaning of what's in your heart.

320
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Look at yourself.

321
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're not angry. You're regretful.

322
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If you were angry, you'd do anything you think of -- Like break random stuff...

323
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But in regret...

324
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You don't have a clue what you can do.

325
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Your heart wants to apologise to him,

326
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But your ego says

327
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Regret is much better.

328
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And if you ask me,

329
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just an ounce of ego

330
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Can ruin this 5'5 girl called Maheen.

331
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Remember...

332
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's suffered two wounds by your hand.

333
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
One on his face,

334
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And one on his heart.

335
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The one on his heart

336
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is the one that pains you.

337
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why'd it pain me?

338
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who's he to me?

339
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But it's Wednesday, Ammi Begum! Not the weekend.

340
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Would you argue with me if I said it's Sunday?

341
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No.

342
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Then, just think

343
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's Sunday.

344
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Fair enough...

345
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why'd you take off your coat?

346
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I ain't going to work today.

347
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

348
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Didn't you hear?

349
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's Sunday.

350
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You called me here?

351
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aye...

352
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I almost forgot...

353
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why don't you

354
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Change and come to the lawn?

355
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

356
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We're playing today.

357
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You too.

358
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't know how to play, Ammi Begum.

359
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
<i>Who said you're playing?</i>

360
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Our umpire, Munshi Alam, had to go out...

361
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Someone's got to fill in...

362
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You didn't ask about the teams playing today.

363
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
May I?

364
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Pray tell.

365
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's Maheen's Losers vs Waqar's Winners!

366
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who named the teams?

367
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Me and Fajr.

368
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Did Maheen make the team? Maheen's Losers?

369
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Of course.

370
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But how?

371
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Like Sunday on Wednesday!

372
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Under Dado's reign,

373
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Days will change,

374
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Dates will change,

375
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And so will hearts.

376
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hmm!

377
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aye...

378
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That 'hmm' reminds me...

379
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Family dinner tonight...

380
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So, after the match...

381
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't slip away, okay?

382
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

383
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We'll fix the date for Maheen and Gulrez's engagement.

384
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hmm!

385
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That 'hmm' also reminds me...

386
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What are we waiting for?

387
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The poor lad's playin' out there all by himself!

388
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mehrunnisa, I don't know

389
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If what Ammi Begum's doing

390
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is right,

391
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But even if not,

392
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
There can be no righter way to do something wrong.

393
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Someone's overstayed her welcome!

394
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Your Dad forbade me from leaving, no matter what you say.

395
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's been here since yesterday.

396
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aye.

397
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He says he ain't going anywhere until you do as he says.

398
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Give him something to eat

399
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And tell him

400
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll hear his story after breakfast.

401
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Get in, Fajr.

402
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't think she's coming.

403
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She is.

404
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Nano's asked her to.

405
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She won't say no to her.

406
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Actually, that's just an excuse.

407
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She really wants to play cricket this time.

408
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I thought she said Nano's place stings at her.

409
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And

410
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That she's never playing cricket again?

411
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
D'you know what it means to play cricket?

412
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Decisions change every moment.

413
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's what she's been doing all this time.

414
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You better be talking about cricket.

415
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No.

416
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm talking about second thoughts.

417
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Like in cricket.

418
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
One ball you hit a six,

419
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And the next one bowls you out.

420
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The situation changes every moment.

421
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You can lose a match you've almost won.

422
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So,

423
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Until the last ball's been thrown,

424
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You never think you've won.

425
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And...

426
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Look who we have here!

427
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's she having second thoughts about?

428
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Let's just say... Our star player's out of retirement!

429
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Go.

430
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
C'mon! Double time!

431
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
C'mon, let's go!

432
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Here!

433
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Second time I'm on leave.

434
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sometimes, you got to. For the one you love.

435
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So... Doesn't Wali love you?

436
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We've got married,

437
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That ain't that good an option now.

438
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You comin' or arguing about it here?

439
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You know

440
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm not a good cricketer.

441
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
They all play to win.

442
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
They all lose when they don't play.

443
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Come!

444
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
By the way,

445
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How do I look?

446
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Like a cricketer!

447
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Come on now!

448
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's going to be fun! You've got to beat everyone!

449
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Tell me any story you want and be done with it.

450
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've decided

451
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
To listen to everything you say today.

452
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What do you think?

453
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
All this pleading before you

454
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Is

455
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just to tell you some story?

456
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The truth is

457
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Even now, my heart does not want

458
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
To dig up

459
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Your mother's grave before you.

460
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Her reckoning is out of my control now.

461
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I can't bear

462
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
To stand before my daughter

463
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
As the culprit.

464
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Act 1, scene 1... Go on...

465
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's that?

466
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
They're the letters

467
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Your mother wrote to her beloved.

468
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You need to read them

469
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Before I begin.

470
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Waqar Ahmed,

471
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Fajr Aurangzeb,

472
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mehrunnisa Dastoor, and Ali Dastoor.

473
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Announcing now the lineup for Maheen's Losers,

474
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who named my team?

475
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's the jury's decision.

476
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're 'Maheen's Losers' until you win.

477
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We'll see about that. Announce the lineup.

478
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Gulrez will be playing for me.

